1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the use of P2P networks for mobile web service discovery, which falls under the domain of distributed computing. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the use of JXTA modules for publishing mobile web services, which involves the use of data structures and algorithms for efficient discovery. 
3. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes an alternate approach to UDDI registry for discovering mobile web services, which falls under the domain of software engineering. 
4. cs.Distributed - The paper discusses the use of P2P networks for mobile web service discovery, which falls under the domain of distributed systems. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the use of P2P networks for mobile web service discovery, which involves the sharing of resources and information among peers, falling under the domain of social and information networks.
